HB 337 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Beaullieu
Abstract: Increases the number of special bingo sessions that may be annually conducted
by a licensed organization from two sessions to four sessions.
Present law allows the office of charitable gaming to issue a special license for the conduct
of not more than two bingo sessions per year.
Proposed law increases the number of bingo games under the special license from two
sessions per year to four sessions per year.
Effective upon signature of governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
(Amends R.S. 4:710(A))
